The Adamawa State Emergency Management Agency (ADSEMA) has began the distribution of 1,800 bags of 50kg foreign rice released by the Nigerian Customs Service (NCS). Dr Muhammad Suleiman, the Executive Secretary of the Agency made this known Tuesday in Yola, saying the distribution covers the 21  LGAs of the state. Suleiman said a standing distribution committee have been constituted to ensure even sharing of the palliatives across the 226 wards. He stressed that Governor Ahmadu Fintiri  had directed the immediate distribution to cushion the effects of the COVID-19 in the state. “Chairmen, word councillors and some elders are members of the committee to ensure even sharing” he added. Mr Kamaldeen Olumoh, the Comptroller of Customs, Adamawa/Taraba command said, the 1800 bags of foreign was released inline with CG Hameed Ali directives to counter the effect of COVID-19 in the state. 